@page
@model ITWebsite.Pages.PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<section class="py-5">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-8">

                <h1 class="fw-bold section-title mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>

                <p class="text-secondary">
                    Effective Date: @DateTime.Now.ToString("MMMM dd, yyyy")
                </p>

                <h5 class="fw-semibold mt-4">1. Who We Are</h5>
                <p>
                    Kairos Technologies is an independent residential IT support service provider based in Calgary, Alberta.
                    We provide technical support services for individuals and families.
                </p>
                <p>
                    If you have any privacy-related questions, please contact:
                    <br />
                    James Hsu<br />
                    info@kairostech.ca<br />
                    Calgary, Alberta, Canada
                </p>

                <h5 class="fw-semibold mt-4">2. Information We Collect</h5>
                <p>When you contact us, we may collect:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Your name</li>
                    <li>Email address</li>
                    <li>Phone number</li>
                    <li>Description of your technical issue</li>
                    <li>Device or network details you voluntarily provide</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    We do not intentionally collect sensitive personal information unless it is necessary
                    to provide the requested service.
                </p>

                <h5 class="fw-semibold mt-4">3. How We Use Your Information</h5>
                <p>Your information is used only to:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Respond to inquiries</li>
                    <li>Provide requested IT services</li>
                    <li>Schedule appointments</li>
                    <li>Communicate about your service</li>
                    <li>Issue invoices and maintain business records</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information.
                </p>

                <h5 class="fw-semibold mt-4">4. Data Storage</h5>
                <p>
                    Information submitted through the contact form or email may be stored in secure email systems
                    and basic business records for documentation and accounting purposes.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Reasonable steps are taken to protect your information, however no method of electronic
                    transmission or storage is completely secure.
                </p>

                <h5 class="fw-semibold mt-4">5. Remote Support Sessions</h5>
                <p>
                    If you authorize remote support, you consent to temporary access to your device for the purpose
                    of performing the requested service. You may terminate the session at any time.
                </p>
                <p>
                    We access only what is reasonably necessary to complete the work and do not intentionally
                    retain personal files unrelated to the service.
                </p>

                <h5 class="fw-semibold mt-4">6. Third-Party Services</h5>
                <p>
                    Our website may be hosted using third-party infrastructure providers. These providers may
                    process technical data such as IP addresses as part of normal website operation.
                </p>
                <p>
                    We do not share personal information with third parties except as required by law.
                </p>

                <h5 class="fw-semibold mt-4">7. Retention of Information</h5>
                <p>
                    Client records are retained only as long as necessary for service documentation,
                    accounting, and legal compliance.
                </p>

                <h5 class="fw-semibold mt-4">8. Your Rights</h5>
                <p>
                    You may request access to your personal information or request corrections by contacting us directly.
                </p>

                <h5 class="fw-semibold mt-4">9. Changes to This Policy</h5>
                <p>
                    This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically. Updates will be posted on this page with a revised effective date.
                </p>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>